---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const updated = 'June 1, 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Use — PaycheckCalc"
  description="Terms and conditions for using PaycheckCalc. Read our disclaimer, limitations of liability, and acceptable use policy."
>
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
      <p>Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container page-body">
    <div class="prose">
      <p class="intro">
        By accessing or using PaycheckCalc ("the Site"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Use.
        If you do not agree, please do not use the Site.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Informational Purpose Only</h2>
      <p>
        PaycheckCalc provides paycheck and tax estimates for <strong>informational and educational purposes only</strong>.
        The calculations are based on publicly available federal and state tax data and standard assumptions.
        Results are estimates and <strong>do not constitute tax advice, legal advice, or financial advice</strong>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Always consult a qualified tax professional, CPA, or the IRS/state Department of Revenue for
        authoritative guidance on your specific tax situation.
      </p>

      <h2>2. No Warranty</h2>
      <p>
        The Site and its content are provided on an "AS IS" and "AS AVAILABLE" basis without warranties
        of any kind, express or implied. We do not warrant that:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>The results of the calculator are accurate, complete, or current</li>
        <li>The Site will be uninterrupted, error-free, or free of viruses</li>
        <li>Any specific result will meet your requirements</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Tax laws change frequently. While we strive to keep our data current, we cannot guarantee that
        all rates, brackets, and deductions reflect the most recent legislation.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, PaycheckCalc and its operators shall not be
        liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from
        your use of or reliance on the Site, including but not limited to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Errors or inaccuracies in tax estimates</li>
        <li>Tax penalties or underpayments resulting from reliance on our calculator</li>
        <li>Loss of data or interruption of service</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Acceptable Use</h2>
      <p>You agree not to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use the Site for any unlawful purpose</li>
        <li>Attempt to scrape, crawl, or extract data in bulk without permission</li>
        <li>Interfere with or disrupt the Site's infrastructure</li>
        <li>Reproduce or redistribute the Site's content for commercial purposes without consent</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        All content, code, and design on this Site are owned by PaycheckCalc or its licensors.
        You may use the calculator for personal, non-commercial purposes. Republishing or creating
        derivative works without express written permission is prohibited.
      </p>

      <h2>6. External Links</h2>
      <p>
        The Site may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for the content
        or privacy practices of those sites. Links do not imply endorsement.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Changes to Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We reserve the right to update these Terms at any time. Changes become effective upon posting.
        Continued use of the Site after changes means you accept the updated Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Governing Law</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms are governed by the laws of the United States. Any disputes shall be resolved
        in the applicable courts.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these Terms? <a href="/contact">Contact us</a> or email hello@paycheck-calc.com.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a56db 0%, #1447c0 100%);
    color: #fff;
    padding: 48px 20px 44px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .page-hero h1 { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .page-hero p  { opacity: .78; font-size: 0.9rem; }

  .page-body { max-width: 760px; padding-top: 48px; padding-bottom: 64px; }
  .intro { font-size: 1rem; color: #374151; line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 32px; padding: 18px 20px; background: #fff8e1; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #f59e0b; }

  .prose h2 { font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; margin: 32px 0 10px; color: #111827; }
  .prose p  { color: #374151; line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 14px; font-size: 0.925rem; }
  .prose ul { margin: 0 0 14px 24px; }
  .prose li { color: #374151; line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 4px; font-size: 0.925rem; }
  .prose strong { color: #111827; }
  .prose a { color: #1a56db; }
</style>
